      "body" : "Just checked and found out that QT does not support custom or secure allocators. It would required to dig down the whole path to the OS implementation (for the three supported platforms) which would be hard to implement and very hard to maintain (not only that it runs also that it is secure).\r\n\r\nThe separated secure entry process would make more sense but even there its not trivial to implement.\r\n\r\nMaybe wallet encryption should go more into a direction of easy-multisig-usage or other concepts of store partial data in a \"cold-space\".",
