      "body" : "Looking deeper, it seems that if you lock the return of the data accessor(\r\nui->passEdit1->text().data() ) it properly locks the area of memory being\r\nused to store the actual data. I verified this in GDB.\r\n\r\nI also changed the locking done for RPC calls so it locks the proper\r\nmemory, again verified in GDB.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/micrictor/bitcoin/commit/ad32eff00df2a452c6bb36e4d46dba9ea109d14e\r\n\r\nI'm unsure how allocation works with QStrings, is there more that needs to be done then simply locking the storage location?\r\n\r\n",
